  
                    
                        
                
                
            Former South Africa international Naka Drotske, a member of the 1995 World Cup winning squad, is in a critical condition in hospital after being shot during a robbery in Pretoria.The 47-year-old was with former Springbok team-mate Os du Randt, but the latter was not injured.Drotske played one game during South Africa's home World Cup victory.
    
        
It was the first major sporting event to take place in the country following the end of apartheid.More to follow.
 
